  <prompt>
    Update `FeedTodoSyncContext` cross-block sync events to carry `todoId` instead of `eventId`. Update both producers (TodoDetail, KanbanBoard) and consumers (LegalWorkspace ActivityFeed, SmartToDo widget) accordingly. Verify mutating a `sprk_todo` in one block updates the other within one render cycle.
  </prompt>

  <role>Spaarke shared-context developer.</role>

  <goal>`FeedTodoSyncContext` payload shape is todo-id-keyed; producers + consumers updated; LegalWorkspace ActivityFeed and SmartToDo widget stay in sync.</goal>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="FR-14">Cross-block sync uses todo-id; one render cycle propagation; no stale state across blocks.</constraint>
    <constraint source="OS-1">No event-id compat path.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/contexts/FeedTodoSyncContext.ts</file>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/ActivityFeed/</file>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/SmartToDo/</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Update `FeedTodoSyncContext` payload type from `eventId` to `todoId`.</step>
    <step order="2">Update every producer call site (TodoDetail save, KanbanBoard drag-end).</step>
    <step order="3">Update every consumer subscriber (LegalWorkspace ActivityFeed, SmartToDo widget).</step>
    <step order="4">Manual cross-block test: mutate a `sprk_todo` in SmartTodo; verify LegalWorkspace ActivityFeed updates within one render cycle.</step>
    <step order="5">Unit tests for the context payload shape.</step>
    <step order="6">Run `npm run build` + `npm test`. Fluent v9 lint pass.</step>
    <step order="7">Update TASK-INDEX.md status to ✅ completed.</step>
  </steps>

  <outputs>
